The paper proposes a novel method for RGB-D facial recognition using attention layers and deep neural networks. This work involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image processing, feature extraction, and classification. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as transfer learning and deep neural networks, which are covered in sub-categories such as cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, and cs.NE.
